From: Santosh Y <santosh.sy@samsung.com>
Date: Thu, 29 May 2014 10:01:52 +0530
Subject: NVMe: Prevent possible NULL pointer dereference
References: bnc#913030,FATE#317455
Patch-Mainline: v3.17
Git-commit: 6808c5fb7fc1574c7608a38c9819f1639d89c3d0

kmalloc() used by the nvme_alloc_iod() to allocate memory for 'iod'
can fail. So check the return value.

Signed-off-by: Santosh Y <santosh.sy@samsung.com>
Signed-off-by: Matthew Wilcox <matthew.r.wilcox@intel.com>
Acked-by: Hannes Reinecke <hare@suse.de>
---
 drivers/block/nvme-core.c | 5 ++++-
 1 file changed, 4 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/drivers/block/nvme-core.c b/drivers/block/nvme-core.c
index 1c0cbc9..37189e8 100644
--- a/drivers/block/nvme-core.c
+++ b/drivers/block/nvme-core.c
@@ -1563,7 +1563,11 @@ struct nvme_iod *nvme_map_user_pages(struct nvme_dev *dev, int write,
 		goto put_pages;
 	}
 
+	err = -ENOMEM;
 	iod = nvme_alloc_iod(count, length, GFP_KERNEL);
+	if (!iod)
+		goto put_pages;
+
 	sg = iod->sg;
 	sg_init_table(sg, count);
 	for (i = 0; i < count; i++) {
@@ -1576,7 +1580,6 @@ struct nvme_iod *nvme_map_user_pages(struct nvme_dev *dev, int write,
 	sg_mark_end(&sg[i - 1]);
 	iod->nents = count;
 
-	err = -ENOMEM;
 	nents = dma_map_sg(&dev->pci_dev->dev, sg, count,
 				write ? DMA_TO_DEVICE : DMA_FROM_DEVICE);
 	if (!nents)
